Denote by $f(x)$ the trigo part\[f(x)=2\sin{x}\sin{1}[1 + \sec (x-1) \sec (x+1)]\]
\end{think}

\begin{answer}
$\sin$ angle addition formula,
\begin{align*}
f(x)&=2\sin{x}\sin(1)\left(\frac1{\cos{x-1}}+\frac1{\cos{x+1}}\right)\\
&=\frac{2\sin x\sin(1)}{\cos(x-1)\cos(x+1)}\\
&=\frac{\sin(2x)-\sin(1)}{\cos(2x)-\cos(2)}\\
&=\frac{\sin(\theta)}{\cos(\phi)}
\end{align*}where $\theta\equiv 2x-1\pmod{180}$ and $\phi\equiv 2x+1\pmod{180}$. In terms of $\phi$, $f(x)$ is equivalent to \[\sum_{n=1}^4(-1)^n\frac{\sin\left(\frac{180}{2}-\frac{\phi}2\right)}{\cos\left(\frac{\phi}2\right)}\]where $\phi\in[1,91]$.

We require the sum of degrees. Since there is one value for each degree, the answer is $4\cdot 90=\boxed{360}$.
</answer>

